ey did them after overcoming attachments and with an equanimo=\r\nus mind.\n\n \n\nAs I keep saying, what you do is a secondary factor and how yo=\r\nu do it is primary. Even as we engage in actions that we believe to be our =\r\ndharma, we should work on our attitude and increase surrender. When one has=\r\n surrendered to god and is able to look at pleasure and pain, praise and ce=\r\nnsure in the same way, then one&#39;s dharma will be far clearer to one. One wh=\r\nose mind is densely conditioned by duality and desires will see one&#39;s dharm=\r\na through the coloring of that conditioning and may misjudge. On the other =\r\nhand, one with a clear mind with very little conditioning will see one&#39;s dh=\r\narma clearer.\n\n \n\nIn simpler words, one who heavily identifies with the bod=\r\ny and wants comforts and pleasures of the body will see one&#39;s dharma from t=\r\nhat motivation. One may identify with body, with a group of people, with a =\r\ndeity etc. As is the identification, so is the conditioning and so is one&#39;s=\r\n vision of one&#39;s dharma.\n\n \n\nThough everyone is playing their allotted role=\r\n, some have densely conditioned minds and unable to see their dharma clearl=\r\ny and pursuing adharma. As a result, they may continue to be allotted roles=\r\n where densely conditioned minds restrict their actions, in future.\n\n \n\nSom=\r\ne have very clear minds and able to see their dharma clearly and pursuing h=\r\nigher dharma. As a result, they may continue to allotted roles where lighte=\r\nr and lighter mental conditioning restricts them and eventually they become=\r\n free.\n\n \n\nOne can try to use free will to move from the former case to the=\r\n latter case.\n\n \n\nBest regards,\n\nNarasimha\n\n------------ --------- --------=\r\n- --------- --------- --------- -\n\n  Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Le=\r\nssons, Jyotish Writings,\n\n&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam a=\r\nnd Pitri Tarpana:\n\n       